```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>My Joke Website</title>

  <style>
    body {
      background-color: #ffffff;
      font-family: sans-serif;
      font-size: 16px;
    }

    .joke-container {
      margin: 0 auto;
      width: 400px;
      padding: 20px;
      background-color: #eee;
    }

    .joke {
      margin-bottom: 10px;
    }

    .joke-punchline {
      display: none;
    }

    .push-to-reveal {
      background-color: #000;
      color: #fff;
      padding: 10px;
      cursor: pointer;
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>

<div class="joke-container">
  <h1>My Joke Website</h1>

  <div class="joke">
    <p>What do you call a fish with no eyes? Fsh!</p>
    <button class="push-to-reveal">Push to reveal punchline</button>
  </div>

  <div class="joke">
    <p>Why did the scarecrow win an award? Because he was outstanding in his field!</p>
    <button class="push-to-reveal">Push to reveal punchline</button>
  </div>
</div>

<script>
  var jokeContainers = document.querySelectorAll(".joke-container");

  for (var i = 0; i < jokeContainers.length; i++) {
    var jokeContainer = jokeContainers[i];
    var joke = jokeContainer.querySelector(".joke");
    var punchlineButton = jokeContainer.querySelector(".push-to-reveal");

    punchlineButton.addEventListener("click", function() {
      joke.querySelector(".joke-punchline").style.display = "block";
    });
  }
</script>

</body>
</html>
```

This code creates a simple website with two joke blocks. Each joke block has a joke and a button that reveals the punchline. The `push-to-reveal` button uses JavaScript to toggle the visibility of the `joke-punchline` element.

To replace the jokes with your own, simply edit the `joke` elements in the HTML code. You can also add more jokes by adding more `joke-container` elements to the HTML code.

To make the website more colorful, you can change the background color of the `joke-container` elements and the color of the text. You can also add some CSS animations to make the website more visually appealing.

